    text "So bioacoustics is basically the study of sound in biological systems&#8212;how animals produce, perceive, and use sound to communicate, navigate, and interact with their environment"
  ]
  node [
    id 1
    label "1"
    text " It&#8217;s not just about birdsong or whale calls&#8212;it includes insects, amphibians, even plants reacting to vibration"
  ]
  node [
    id 2
    label "2"
    text " We use all sorts of tools&#8212;hydrophones for underwater species, directional microphones, long-term acoustic sensors&#8212;to capture and analyze these sounds"
  ]
  node [
    id 3
    label "3"
    text " Then we apply machine learning and signal processing to pick apart patterns"
  ]
  node [
    id 4
    label "4"
    text " What&#8217;s being said, how often, and under what conditions? A lot of current work focuses on ecological monitoring"
  ]
  node [
    id 5
    label "5"
    text " By listening to a forest or a reef, we can gauge biodiversity without even seeing the animals"
  ]
  node [
    id 6
    label "6"
    text " It&#8217;s fast, noninvasive, and scalable"
  ]
  node [
    id 7
    label "7"
    text " Passive acoustic monitoring is becoming a key part of conservation science"
  ]
  node [
    id 8
    label "8"
    text " There&#8217;s also the impact of human-generated sound&#8212;what we call anthropogenic noise"
  ]
  node [
